creator: Lab4U
descriptionHtml:
"Lab4Physics makes it easy and inexpensive to bring fun and engaging lab experiences into the classroom!

The Lab4Physics app uses built-in sensors found in smartphones and tablets to transform your mobile device into a powerful science lab that can be used flexibly by teachers and students alike. Students can use the accelerometer, sonometer, camera, and a speedometer to gather, vizualize and analize data, or use pre-designed, inquiry-based experiments to explore concepts like movement, gravity, acceleration, force, energy, rotation, torque, and waves.

Lab4Physics puts a lab in every student's pocket and transforms physics from theoretically intense to intensely fun!"
descriptionShort: Lab4Physics turns phones into pocket labs, putting science at your fingertips.

- We have updated our Privacy Policy and Terms & Conditions.
- Improved bug fix procedures and performance enhancement.

creator: Lab4U
descriptionHtml:
Lab4U transforms the way science--biology, physics, and chemistry--is learned and taught. With Lab4U, you can turn your phone into a powerful scientific tool that allows you to experiment in real time using different parts of your device, like the camera, microphone, motion sensor, and more.

Lab4U uses inquiry-based learning to make science come to life in real time. Explore and analyze images of nature using Lab4U Biology, determine the color and concentration of chemical reactions with Lab4Chemistry, and analyze the force and acceleration of a moving object with Lab4Physics. Find each of these experiments in the Labs section of the app.

Lab4U's tools and experiments are also aligned with educational curriculum, meaning you can carry out incredible, deep learning experiences while enhancing scientific thinking in an easy, fun, and novel way. Meanwhile, you'll build and strengthen the STEM-focused skill set required for thriving in tomorrow's workforce.

Download the new Lab4U app and experiment with us!

Explore and analyze images of nature using Lab4U Biology, determine the color and concentration of chemical reactions with Lab4Chemistry, and analyze the force and acceleration of a moving object with Lab4Physics. Find each of these experiments in the Labs section of the app.

Lab4U's tools and experiments are also aligned with educational curriculum, meaning you can carry out incredible, deep learning experiences while enhancing scientific thinking in an easy, fun, and novel way. Meanwhile, you'll build and strengthen the STEM-focused skill set required for thriving in tomorrow's workforce.

Download the new Lab4U app and experiment with us!
